rne.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I can make it!</span><hr size=1> Times are still up in the air, but preliminarily they will be insertion around 8-9pm (pacific) on Friday night with the actual raid beginning 10am pacific on Saturday.<br>
<br>
The insertion time is dependant on two things, first, how many people we get to show up.  If we get enough of the raid that shows up Friday for insertion then we will insert then and save ourselves a passle of trouble.  Second, the guild that is signed up for the plane on Friday.  What actual time we can insert depends entirely on how much plane is cleared by the guild that is in there.  If they are on the ball and get started in the early afternoon or something then we will be ready to insert in the 8-9pm range (pacific), if they don't get started till about then....&lt;shrug&gt;<br>
<br>
Inserting the night before is vastly preferable to a break in.  As of this moment I only know of one wizard that is available for getting us ported up there (my wife).  That means that all the mobs in the world will have to be faced by 5 people at a time.  In all the Hate raids I have done I have never actually had to do a break in, I don't quite know what to expect.<br>
<br>
If we do insert the night before and you can't make it then, but will be able to make the raid we should be able to get you ported up the morning of the raid.  You *will* die on insertion.  There is no way around that.  When you get aggro, stop, /loc, and die.  When you reappear at your bind point, /consent the CR team (hopefully we have a rogue dumb..er..brave enough to volunteer) and wait patiently for a res.  Do not go watch tv, do not go off and bake a cake from scratch, just sit there and wait patiently.  It may take a while, but we will get you in camp and res'd.<br>
<br>
One thing that is *MANDATORY*, if you can't gate/port yourself, you *MUST* go work up your pottery and make or buy a gate potion of some kind.  If you can't get yourself out of the plane and you need to leave early you must have your own means of exit.  Thurgadin gate potions are simple to make, they cost about 30-40p for working up pottery, and about an hour to gather materials.  Details on the gate potion itself can be found at Allakhazam's in the Thurgadin Quests listing, the title of the quest is &quot;Saving Tanik&quot; it is the 4th prayer shawl quest.  Gate potions to Everfrost, Innothule, or Field of Bone can be purchased from your neighborhood alchemist for 300-400p.  Either method is preferable to being stuck somewhere you can't walk out of.<br>
<br>
I would also strongly encourage you to track down a map of Hate (no, not at eqatlas unfortunately) and familiarize yourself with the route from the zone in point to the camp.  It isn't complicated, but the fewer times I have to give out directions the happier I will be.  <br>
<br>
You may also wish to print out a list of what drops and know in advance if you need a particular item (i.e. I don't need boots, I have better already).  While on the raid, do *NOT* ask when we will be pulling, or how many of MobX are left.  The puller does NOT take requests, they pull what they need to.  Be patient and know that our goal is to clear the entire first floor and go up to the second floor so we will be pulling your mob, just not right now.  <br>
<br>
When something drops, pay attention and wait for the Loot Coordinator to call out who gets the item.  If it is you, get over there and loot it asap, don't fiddle around, most of these bodies will only last 8 mins.  Do NOT EVER peek at a corpse to see what is on it.  This only leads to accidental lootings and hard feelings.  The only people that are allowed to loot are those called for the item by the LC, the raid leaders, and the group leader of the group that got experience.  All vendor loot items will be turned over to me and sold at the end of the raid to split the proceeds with the three guilds in attendance.<br>
<br>
Ok, I am done now, simple reply post turned into one of my epic rambles again, sorry.<br>
<br>
Az<br>
